This `always_ff` ternary assignment does not simulate correctly when verilated with `--coverage-line`.  I can work around this by pulling the `? :` out of the `always_ff` block, but I'm trying to figure out what's going wrong here.

I see the problem with the generated C++.  Namely that `t__DOT____Vconcswap_1_hff8df1f0__0` is being used for the ternary result and it is referenced before it is assigned:
```
VL_INLINE_OPT void Vt_cover_line_wide_ternary___024root___nba_sequent__TOP__1(Vt_cover_line_wide_ternary___024root* vlSelf) {
. . .
    // Init
    VlWide<6>/*160:0*/ t__DOT____Vconcswap_1_hff8df1f0__0;
    VL_ZERO_W(161, t__DOT____Vconcswap_1_hff8df1f0__0);
    VlWide<6>/*191:0*/ __Vtemp_2;
    VlWide<6>/*191:0*/ __Vtemp_4;
    // Body
    vlSymsp->TOP__t__DOT__intf_sel.bar = t__DOT____Vconcswap_1_hff8df1f0__0[4U];
. . .
    VL_COND_WIWW(161, t__DOT____Vconcswap_1_hff8df1f0__0, 
                 (1U & vlSelfRef.t__DOT__cyc), ([&]() {
                ++(vlSymsp->__Vcoverage[2]);
            }(), __Vtemp_2), ([&]() {
                ++(vlSymsp->__Vcoverage[3]);
            }(), __Vtemp_4));
```

